of sleep. Whenever possible, give yourself extra time before bed to get ready for sleep."
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"/>
        <ImageView
            android:id="@+id/imageView"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:src="@drawable/sleep"
            android:scaleType="centerCrop"
            android:adjustViewBounds="true"
            android:padding="16dp"/>
        <!-- Advice 5 -->
        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/advice1Title"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="5. Disconnect Devices in the Hour Before Bed"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:textSize="18sp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="8dp"/>

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/advice1Content"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="Tablets, smartphones, and laptops can keep your brain wired, making it hard to truly wind down. The light from these electronic devices can also suppress your natural production of melatonin. As much as possible, try to disconnect for an hour or more before going to bed."
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"/>
        <ImageView
            android:id="@+id/imageView"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:src="@drawable/test"
            android:scaleType="centerCrop"
            android:adjustViewBounds="true"
            android:padding="16dp"/>
        <!-- Advice 6 -->
        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/advice1Title"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="6. Limit Caffeine After 2 p.m."
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:textSize="18sp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="8dp"/>

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/advice1Content"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="Caffeinated drinks, including coffee, tea, and sodas, are among the most popular beverages in the world. Some people are tempted to use the jolt of energy from caffeine to try to overcome daytime sleepiness, but that approach is not sustainable and can cause long-term sleep deprivation. To avoid this, keep an eye on your caffeine intake and avoid it later in the day when it can be a barrier to falling asleep."
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"/>
        <ImageView
            android:id="@+id/imageView"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:src="@drawable/cafeine"
            android:scaleType="centerCrop"
            android:adjustViewBounds="true"
            android:padding="16dp"/>

        <!-- Advice 7 -->
        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/advice1Title"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="7.Limit Nicotine Use and Smoke Exposure"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:textSize="18sp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="8dp"/>

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/advice1Content"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="Exposure to smoke, including secondhand smoke, has been associated with a range of sleeping problems
including difficulty falling asleep and fragmented sleep. Nicotine is a stimulant, and evening nicotine use in particular has been found to disrupt sleep"
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"/>
        <ImageView
            android:id="@+id/imageView"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:src="@drawable/smoke"
            android:scaleType="centerCrop"
            android:adjustViewBounds="true"
            android:padding="16dp"/>

        <!-- Advice 8 -->
        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/advice1Title"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="8.Limit Nicotine Use and Smoke Exposure"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:textSize="18sp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="8dp"/>

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/advice1Content"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="
In addition to improving overall sleep hygiene, you may want to discuss the use of supplements with your doctor. Melatonin supplements are commonly used to shorten the time it takes to fall asleep. Other natural sleep aids include valerian, chamomile, and glycine. Since dietary supplements are not closely regulated by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration, it is important to take steps to ensure you are purchasing reputable sleep supplements."
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"/>
        <ImageView
            android:id="@+id/imageView"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:src="@drawable/supplements"
            android:scaleType="centerCrop"
            android:adjustViewBounds="true"
            android:padding="16dp"/>
        <!-- Advice 9 -->
        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/advice1Title"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="9.Eat Dinner a Few Hours Before Bed"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:textSize="18sp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="8dp"/>

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/advice1Content"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="It can be harder to fall asleep if your body is still digesting a big dinner. To keep food-based sleep disruptions to a minimum, try to avoid late dinners and minimize especially fatty or spicy foods. If you need an evening snack, opt for something light."
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"/>
        <ImageView
            android:id="@+id/imageView"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:src="@drawable/dinner"
            android:scaleType="centerCrop"
            android:adjustViewBounds="true"
            android:padding="16dp"/>
        <!-- Advice 10 -->
        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/advice1Title"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="10.Talk With a Doctor"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:textSize="18sp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="8dp"/>

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/advice1Content"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="Your doctor is in the best position to offer detailed and personalized advice if you experience serious difficulties sleeping. Talk with your doctor if you find that your sleep problems are worsening, persisting over the long-term, affecting your health and safety, or if they occur alongside other unexplained health problems. They can provide additional guidance and treat any underlying conditions."
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"/>
        <ImageView
            android:id="@+id/imageView"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:src="@drawable/doctor"
            android:scaleType="centerCrop"
            android:adjustViewBounds="true"
            android:padding="16dp"/>


    </LinearLayout>
</ScrollView>
